text.section:
The department shall, unless otherwise provided by law, exercise all functions of the state in relation to:
Management of penal, reform, and correctional institutions;
Supervision of probation and parole;
The giving of assistance to other departments, agencies, and institutions of the state and federal government when requested by performing services in conformity with this section;
Acting as the agent of the federal government in matters of mutual concern, and in the administration of any federal funds granted to the state to aid in the performance of any function of this department;
Administration and enforcement of the provisions of KRS Chapter 441 relating to the development and enforcement of jail standards, training of jailers and jail personnel, and jail planning and construction.
